Interpretation: Probability that X has a positive effect on Y
Probability that X has a negative effect on Y among those for whom X=1
Probability that Y=1 is due to X=1 (Attribution)
Probability that X has a positive effect on Y for a case in which W  = 1 (where W is possibly defined post treatment)
Probability that X has a positive effect on Y if  W were set to 1 for cases for which in fact W=0
Probability that X has a positive effect on Y for a case in which W  has a positive effect on Y
Probability of a positive interaction between W and X for Y; the probability that the effect of X on Y is stronger when W is larger
The probability X would have a positive effct on Y if M were controlled to be at the level it would take if X were 1 for units for which in fact M==1
The probability that X causes M and M causes Y among units for which M = 1 and X causes Y
